2. “Orowns enriched with thrice tenfold increase adorn some3 others a double crown adorns; but a triple crown with fruitage heaped up with a hundred twinings adorns thee.'’ Oonstr.: Serta (crowns, garlands) aucta ter denis crementis (increase, fruit) coronat alios, quosdam dupli- cata serta. coronant; te ornant trina fructu cumulata serta centum nexibus. The stanza plainly refers to the Parable of the Sower, some of whose seed falling on good ground “brought forth fruit, some an hundredfold, some sixtyfold, and some thirtyfold'' (Matt. 13, 8). Our Lord Himself explains the meaning of this parable (Matt. 13, 18-23).
